postcontent: FOR SALE: Sig Sauer P220 BDA .45 caliper Slide, Barrel, Guide Rod, Spring combo and 2 original European / Euro Mag Release single stack 7 round Magazine Clips. This is from a SIG P220-Browning Double Action .45 ACP. In 1976 Schweizerische Industrie Gesellschaft (SIG) introduced what would become the P220, manufactured by Sauer. Sig Sauer contracted with Browning Arms Co. to import the gun as the Browning Double Action (BDA). The P220 was initially imported to the US by Browning from 1977-1980 prior to Sig establishing a presence in the US. In 1980 Sig decided to import them into the US on their own and rest is history. Parts are in great shape and the slide has Sig Sauer markings (Browning Arms Co., Morgan Utah & Montreal on the left side) and (Sig Sauer System, Made in W. Germany) on the right side of slide).
